<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-019-114  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 019 114.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Jan 8 1990 v6 n1 p55(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cogent ships fault-tolerant controller. ( Cogent Data TechnologiesInc.) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Cogent Data Technologies Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Cogent Data Technologies Diskmaster (Control board) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFault ToleranceDisk DrivesControl Buses.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Cogent Data Technologies Inc. has started shipping Diskmaster, afault-tolerant disk controller used in the Siemens Information Systems Inc.andO;line of Comfonet/S PC servers.andM;Diskmaster provides LAN environments with drive mirroring for two pairs ofhard disks and offers a transparent &quot;hot fix&quot; of bad media, said CharlesAnderson, president of Cogent in Friday Harbor, Wash.andP;  The hot-fix featureautomatically remaps bad media and duplicates the good copy of data from themirrored drive to ensure complete fault tolerance, he said.andM;&quot;Any application that runs in DOS, OS/2 or LAN Manager benefits from thespeed and fault tolerance without modification,&quot; because the hot-fix anddisk-mirroring functions operate below the BIOS level, said Anderson.andO;Diskmaster supports AT-compatible computers with as many as four hard drivesand two floppy drives with standard ST-506 interfaces and EnhancedSmall-Device Interfaces (ESDI).andM;In a LAN environment, advanced disk algorithms optimize performance bysegregating user requests between the two drives.andP;  The result is a 15 percentto 20 percent speed improvement over LAN servers that lack disk optimizingand mirroring, he said.andM;Alert mechanisms for LAN administrators are built into the Diskmastercontroller.andP;  In case of a critical error, such as the failure of a boot driveto power up the system, the server and the LAN manager terminals are informedthrough a pop-up window.andM;Diskmaster is priced at $595 for the controller and fault-tolerant system.andM;Cogent can be reached at (206) 378-2929.andO;</TEXT></DOC>